note.p:
Pub. L. 115–254, div. J, § 1802, Oct. 5, 2018, 132 Stat. 3533, provided that: “In this division [see section 1801 of Pub. L. 115–254, set out as a Short Title of 2018 Amendment note under section 101 of this title]: “(1) Appropriate committees of congress.—The term ‘appropriate committees of Congress’ means—“(A) the Committee on Commerce, Science, and Transportation of the Senate;
“(B) the Committee on Homeland Security and Governmental Affairs of the Senate;
“(C) the Committee on Homeland Security of the House of Representatives; and
“(D) the Committee on Transportation and Infrastructure of the House of Representatives.
“(2) TSA.—The term ‘TSA’ means the Transportation Security Administration.”
